#. <section class="sutta" id="mn109"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn109:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 109"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 109"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn109:0.2"
msgid "Mahāpuṇṇamasutta"
msgstr "The Longer Discourse on the Full-Moon night"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn109:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, "
"the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā tadahuposathe pannarase puṇṇāya puṇṇamāya "
"rattiyā bhikkhusaṅghaparivuto abbhokāse nisinno hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now, at that time it was the sabbath—the full moon on the fifteenth day—and "
"the Buddha was sitting in the open surrounded by the Saṅgha of monks."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ cīvaraṃ katvā yena bhagavā "
"tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then one of the mendicants got up from their seat, arranged their robe over "
"one shoulder, raised their joined palms toward the Buddha, and said:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:3.2"
msgid ""
"“Puccheyyāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ kiñcideva desaṃ, sace me bhagavā okāsaṃ "
"karoti pañhassa veyyākaraṇāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I’d like to ask the Buddha about a certain point, if you’d take the time to "
"answer.”"

msgctxt "mn109:3.3"
msgid "“Tena hi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, sake āsane nisīditvā puccha yadākaṅkhasī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, mendicant, take your own seat and ask what you wish.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.16"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:3.4"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu sake āsane nisīditvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "That mendicant took his seat and said to the Buddha:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:4.1"
msgid "“ime nu kho, bhante, pañcupādānakkhandhā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "“Sir, are these the five grasping aggregates:"

msgctxt "mn109:4.2"
msgid ""
"rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, "
"saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho”ti?"
msgstr "form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness?”"

msgctxt "mn109:4.3"
msgid "“Ime kho, bhikkhu, pañcupādānakkhandhā, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "“Yes, they are,” replied the Buddha."

msgctxt "mn109:4.4"
msgid ""
"rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, "
"saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:4.5"
msgid ""
"“Sādhu, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā "
"bhagavantaṃ uttariṃ pañhaṃ pucchi:"
msgstr ""
"Saying “Good, sir”, that mendicant approved and agreed with what the Buddha "
"said. Then he asked another question:"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:6.1"
msgid "“ime pana, bhante, pañcupādānakkhandhā kiṃmūlakā”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, what is the root of these five grasping aggregates?”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:5.1"
msgid "“Ime kho, bhikkhu, pañcupādānakkhandhā chandamūlakā”ti. "
msgstr "“These five grasping aggregates are rooted in desire.”"

msgctxt "mn109:5.2"
msgid ""
"“Taṃyeva nu kho, bhante, upādānaṃ te pañcupādānakkhandhā, udāhu aññatra "
"pañcahupādānakkhandhehi upādānan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, is that grasping the exact same thing as the five grasping "
"aggregates? Or is grasping one thing and the five grasping aggregates "
"another?”"

msgctxt "mn109:5.3"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, bhikkhu, taṃyeva upādānaṃ te pañcupādānakkhandhā, nāpi aññatra "
"pañcahupādānakkhandhehi upādānaṃ."
msgstr "“Neither."

msgctxt "mn109:5.4"
msgid ""
"Yo kho, bhikkhu, pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu chandarāgo taṃ tattha upādānan”ti."
msgstr "Rather, the desire and greed for them is the grasping there.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:7.1"
msgid "“Siyā pana, bhante, pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu chandarāgavemattatā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, can there be different kinds of desire and greed for the five "
"grasping aggregates?”"

msgctxt "mn109:7.2"
msgid "“Siyā, bhikkhū”ti bhagavā avoca "
msgstr "“There can,” said the Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn109:7.3"
msgid "“idha, bhikkhu, ekaccassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“It’s when someone thinks:"

msgctxt "mn109:7.4"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃrūpo siyaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, evaṃvedano siyaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, "
"evaṃsañño siyaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, evaṃsaṅkhāro siyaṃ anāgatamaddhānaṃ, "
"evaṃviññāṇo siyaṃ anāgatamaddhānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘In the future, may I be of such form, such feeling, such perception, such "
"choices, and such consciousness!’"

msgctxt "mn109:7.5"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, siyā pañcasu upādānakkhandhesu chandarāgavemattatā”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how there be different kinds of desire and greed for the five "
"grasping aggregates.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.17"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:8.1"
msgid "“Kittāvatā pana, bhante, khandhānaṃ khandhādhivacanaṃ hotī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, what is the scope of the term ‘aggregates’ as applied to the "
"aggregates?”"

msgctxt "mn109:8.2"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ kiñci, bhikkhu, rūpaṃ—atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā, "
"oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā, hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā, yaṃ dūre santike vā—ayaṃ "
"rūpakkhandho."
msgstr ""
"“Any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; "
"coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: this is called the "
"aggregate of form."

msgctxt "mn109:8.3"
msgid ""
"Yā kāci vedanā—atītānāgatapaccuppannā ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā, oḷārikā vā "
"sukhumā vā, hīnā vā paṇītā vā, yā dūre santike vā—ayaṃ vedanākkhandho."
msgstr "Any kind of feeling at all …"

msgctxt "mn109:8.4"
msgid ""
"Yā kāci saññā—atītānāgatapaccuppannā … pe … yā dūre santike vā—ayaṃ "
"saññākkhandho."
msgstr "Any kind of perception at all …"

msgctxt "mn109:8.5"
msgid ""
"Ye keci saṅkhārā—atītānāgatapaccuppannā ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā, oḷārikā vā "
"sukhumā vā, hīnā vā paṇītā vā, ye dūre santike vā—ayaṃ saṅkhārakkhandho."
msgstr "Any kind of choices at all …"

msgctxt "mn109:8.6"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ—atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā, "
"oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā, hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā, yaṃ dūre santike vā—ayaṃ "
"viññāṇakkhandho."
msgstr ""
"Any kind of consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or "
"external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: this is called "
"the aggregate of consciousness."

msgctxt "mn109:8.7"
msgid "Ettāvatā kho, bhikkhu, khandhānaṃ khandhādhivacanaṃ hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s the scope of the term ‘aggregates’ as applied to the aggregates.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:9.1"
msgid "“Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo rūpakkhandhassa paññāpanāya?"
msgstr ""
"“What is the cause, sir, what is the reason why the aggregate of form is "
"found?"

msgctxt "mn109:9.2"
msgid "Ko hetu ko paccayo vedanākkhandhassa paññāpanāya?"
msgstr "What is the cause, what is the reason why the aggregate of feeling …"

msgctxt "mn109:9.3"
msgid "Ko hetu ko paccayo saññākkhandhassa paññāpanāya?"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "mn109:9.4"
msgid "Ko hetu ko paccayo saṅkhārakkhandhassa paññāpanāya?"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "mn109:9.5"
msgid "Ko hetu ko paccayo viññāṇakkhandhassa paññāpanāyā”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness is found?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:9.6"
msgid ""
"“Cattāro kho, bhikkhu, mahābhūtā hetu, cattāro mahābhūtā paccayo "
"rūpakkhandhassa paññāpanāya."
msgstr ""
"“The four primary elements are the reason why the aggregate of form is found."

msgctxt "mn109:9.7"
msgid "Phasso hetu, phasso paccayo vedanākkhandhassa paññāpanāya."
msgstr "Contact is the reason why the aggregates of feeling …"

msgctxt "mn109:9.8"
msgid "Phasso hetu, phasso paccayo saññākkhandhassa paññāpanāya."
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "mn109:9.9"
msgid "Phasso hetu, phasso paccayo saṅkhārakkhandhassa paññāpanāya."
msgstr "and choices are found."

msgctxt "mn109:9.10"
msgid ""
"Nāmarūpaṃ kho, bhikkhu, hetu, nāmarūpaṃ paccayo viññāṇakkhandhassa "
"paññāpanāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Name and form are the reasons why the aggregate of consciousness is found.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya10"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.18"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:10.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ pana, bhante, sakkāyadiṭṭhi hotī”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, how does identity view come about?”"

msgctxt "mn109:10.2"
msgid ""
"“Idha, bhikkhu, assutavā puthujjano ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa akovido "
"ariyadhamme avinīto sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa akovido "
"sappurisadhamme avinīto "
msgstr ""
"“It’s when an uneducated ordinary person has not seen the noble ones, and is "
"neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not "
"seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of "
"the good persons. "

msgctxt "mn109:10.3"
msgid ""
"rūpaṃ attato samanupassati rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ attani vā rūpaṃ rūpasmiṃ vā "
"attānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form."

msgctxt "mn109:10.4"
msgid ""
"vedanaṃ attato samanupassati vedanāvantaṃ vā attānaṃ attani vā vedanaṃ "
"vedanāya vā attānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They regard feeling as self, self as having feeling, feeling in self, or "
"self in feeling."

msgctxt "mn109:10.5"
msgid ""
"saññaṃ attato samanupassati saññāvantaṃ vā attānaṃ attani vā saññaṃ saññāya "
"vā attānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They regard perception as self, self as having perception, perception in "
"self, or self in perception."

msgctxt "mn109:10.6"
msgid ""
"saṅkhāre attato samanupassati saṅkhāravantaṃ vā attānaṃ attani vā saṅkhāre "
"saṅkhāresu vā attānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They regard choices as self, self as having choices, choices in self, or "
"self in choices."

msgctxt "mn109:10.7"
msgid ""
"viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ attani vā viññāṇaṃ "
"viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They regard consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, "
"consciousness in self, or self in consciousness."

msgctxt "mn109:10.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, sakkāyadiṭṭhi hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how identity view comes about.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya11"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:11.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃ pana, bhante, sakkāyadiṭṭhi na hotī”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, how does identity view not come about?”"

msgctxt "mn109:11.2"
msgid ""
"“Idha, bhikkhu, sutavā ariyasāvako ariyānaṃ dassāvī ariyadhammassa kovido "
"ariyadhamme suvinīto sappurisānaṃ dassāvī sappurisadhammassa kovido "
"sappurisadhamme suvinīto "
msgstr ""
"“It’s when an educated noble disciple has seen the noble ones, and is "
"skilled and trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve seen good "
"persons, and are skilled and trained in the teaching of the good persons. "

msgctxt "mn109:11.3"
msgid ""
"na rūpaṃ attato samanupassati na rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ na attani vā rūpaṃ na "
"rūpasmiṃ vā attānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They don’t regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self "
"in form."

msgctxt "mn109:11.4"
msgid ""
"na vedanaṃ attato samanupassati na vedanāvantaṃ vā attānaṃ na attani vā "
"vedanaṃ na vedanāya vā attānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They don’t regard feeling as self, self as having feeling, feeling in self, "
"or self in feeling."

msgctxt "mn109:11.5"
msgid ""
"na saññaṃ attato samanupassati na saññāvantaṃ vā attānaṃ na attani vā saññaṃ "
"na saññāya vā attānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They don’t regard perception as self, self as having perception, perception "
"in self, or self in perception."

msgctxt "mn109:11.6"
msgid ""
"na saṅkhāre attato samanupassati na saṅkhāravantaṃ vā attānaṃ na attani vā "
"saṅkhāre na saṅkhāresu vā attānaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"They don’t regard choices as self, self as having choices, choices in self, "
"or self in choices."

msgctxt "mn109:11.7"
msgid ""
"na viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati na viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ na attani vā "
"viññāṇaṃ na viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They don’t regard consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, "
"consciousness in self, or self in consciousness."

msgctxt "mn109:11.8"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, sakkāyadiṭṭhi na hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how identity view does not come about.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya12"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:12.1"
msgid "“Ko nu kho, bhante, rūpe assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, what’s the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes "
"to form,"

msgctxt "mn109:12.2"
msgid "Ko vedanāya assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ?"
msgstr "feeling,"

msgctxt "mn109:12.3"
msgid "Ko saññāya assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ?"
msgstr "perception,"

msgctxt "mn109:12.4"
msgid "Ko saṅkhāresu assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ?"
msgstr "choices,"

msgctxt "mn109:12.5"
msgid "Ko viññāṇe assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan”ti?"
msgstr "and consciousness?”"

#. VAR: Yaṃ kho → yañca (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn109:12.6"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ kho, bhikkhu, rūpaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ rūpe "
"assādo."
msgstr ""
"“The pleasure and happiness that arise from form: this is its gratification."

msgctxt "mn109:12.7"
msgid "Yaṃ rūpaṃ aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, ayaṃ rūpe ādīnavo."
msgstr ""
"That form is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback."

msgctxt "mn109:12.8"
msgid "Yo rūpe chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ rūpe nissaraṇaṃ."
msgstr "Removing and giving up desire and greed for form: this is its escape."

msgctxt "mn109:12.9"
msgid "Yaṃ kho, bhikkhu, vedanaṃ paṭicca …"
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from feeling …"

msgctxt "mn109:12.10"
msgid "saññaṃ paṭicca …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "mn109:12.11"
msgid "saṅkhāre paṭicca …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "mn109:12.12"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ viññāṇe assādo."
msgstr "consciousness: this is its gratification."

msgctxt "mn109:12.13"
msgid "Yaṃ viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, ayaṃ viññāṇe ādīnavo."
msgstr ""
"That consciousness is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its "
"drawback."

msgctxt "mn109:12.14"
msgid ""
"Yo viññāṇe chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ viññāṇe nissaraṇan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Removing and giving up desire and greed for consciousness: this is its "
"escape.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya13"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.19"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:13.1"
msgid ""
"“Kathaṃ pana, bhante, jānato kathaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye "
"bahiddhā ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na hontī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, how does one know and see so that there’s no ego, possessiveness, or "
"underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body and all external "
"stimuli?”"

msgctxt "mn109:13.2"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ kiñci, bhikkhu, rūpaṃ—atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā "
"oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā—sabbaṃ rūpaṃ "
"‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya "
"passati."
msgstr ""
"“One truly sees any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; internal "
"or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: <em>all</em> "
"form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not "
"my self.’"

msgctxt "mn109:13.3"
msgid "Yā kāci vedanā …"
msgstr "One truly sees any kind of feeling …"

msgctxt "mn109:13.4"
msgid "yā kāci saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "mn109:13.5"
msgid "ye keci saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "mn109:13.6"
msgid ""
"yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ—atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ "
"vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā—sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ ‘"
"netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti—evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya "
"passati."
msgstr ""
"consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse "
"or fine; inferior or superior; far or near, <em>all</em> consciousness—with "
"right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "mn109:13.7"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, bhikkhu, jānato evaṃ passato imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye bahiddhā "
"ca sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na hontī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how to know and see so that there’s no ego, possessiveness, or "
"underlying tendency to conceit for this conscious body and all external "
"stimuli.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya14"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:14.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññatarassa bhikkhuno evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi:"
msgstr "Now at that time one of the mendicants had the thought:"

msgctxt "mn109:14.2"
msgid ""
"“iti kira, bho, rūpaṃ anattā, vedanā anattā, saññā anattā, saṅkhārā anattā, "
"viññāṇaṃ anattā;"
msgstr ""
"“So it seems, good sir, that form, feeling, perception, choices, and "
"consciousness are not-self."

msgctxt "mn109:14.3"
msgid "anattakatāni kammāni kamattānaṃ phusissantī”ti?"
msgstr "Then what self will the deeds done by not-self affect?”"

msgctxt "mn109:14.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā tassa bhikkhuno cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya bhikkhū "
"āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha, knowing what that monk was thinking, addressed the "
"mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn109:14.5"
msgid ""
"“ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, vijjati yaṃ idhekacco moghapuriso avidvā "
"avijjāgato taṇhādhipateyyena cetasā satthu sāsanaṃ atidhāvitabbaṃ maññeyya:"
msgstr ""
"“It’s possible that some foolish person here—unknowing and ignorant, their "
"mind dominated by craving—thinks they can overstep the teacher’s "
"instructions. They think:"

msgctxt "mn109:14.6"
msgid ""
"‘iti kira, bho, rūpaṃ anattā, vedanā anattā, saññā anattā, saṅkhārā anattā, "
"viññāṇaṃ anattā;"
msgstr ""
"‘So it seems, good sir, that form, feeling, perception, choices, and "
"consciousness are not-self."

msgctxt "mn109:14.7"
msgid "anattakatāni kammāni kamattānaṃ phusissantī’ti."
msgstr "Then what self will the deeds done by not-self affect?’"

# Reading patipucchavinita along with SN 22.82
#. VAR: Paṭivinītā → paṭicca vinītā (bj, pts1) | paṭipucchā vinītā (s1, s2) | paṭipucchāmi vinītā (s3, km)
msgctxt "mn109:14.8"
msgid "Paṭivinītā kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, tatra tatra dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"Now, mendicants, you have been educated by me in questioning with regard to "
"all these things in all such cases."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya15"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.20"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:15.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "mn109:15.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "mn109:15.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn109:15.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "mn109:15.5"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn109:15.6"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "mn109:15.7"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "mn109:15.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya16"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:16.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "“What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "mn109:16.2"
msgid "vedanā …"
msgstr "Is feeling …"

msgctxt "mn109:16.3"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "mn109:16.4"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "mn109:16.5"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "mn109:16.6"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn109:16.7"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "mn109:16.8"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn109:16.9"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "mn109:16.10"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "mn109:16.11"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "mn109:16.12"
msgid ""
"“Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā "
"bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā "
"sabbaṃ rūpaṃ: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“So you should truly see any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; "
"internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: "
"<em>all</em> form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not "
"this, this is not my self.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya17"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:17.1"
msgid "Yā kāci vedanā …"
msgstr "You should truly see any kind of feeling …"

msgctxt "mn109:17.2"
msgid "yā kāci saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "mn109:17.3"
msgid "ye keci saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "mn109:17.4"
msgid ""
"yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ "
"vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ: ‘"
"netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya "
"daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse "
"or fine; inferior or superior; far or near, <em>all</em> consciousness—with "
"right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "mn109:17.5"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpasmimpi nibbindati, vedanāyapi "
"nibbindati, saññāyapi nibbindati, saṅkhāresupi nibbindati, viññāṇasmimpi "
"nibbindati;"
msgstr ""
"Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with form, "
"feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya18"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:18.1"
msgid ""
"nibbindaṃ virajjati, virāgā vimuccati. Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "mn109:18.2"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "mn109:18.3"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn109:18.4"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn109:18.5"
msgid ""
"Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne saṭṭhimattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ "
"anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsūti."
msgstr ""
"And while this discourse was being spoken, the minds of sixty mendicants "
"were freed from defilements by not grasping."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn109:18.6"
msgid "Mahāpuṇṇamasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
